latestPosts.caption:
!! MEN'S FASHION !!
.
"Diljeet looks dapper in a designer multi-colored printing suit set "
.
.
The history of coats is deeply rooted in military and naval backgrounds. The garment has several origin stories, but the researchers point to the origins in the late 19th century. Mainly the British navy and cricket culture popularised the jacket. 

The blazer had its first major revival in the 50’s when the students of the rowing clubs of universities adopted the naval style of clothing. Rowers started wearing the jackets on dry land as a status symbol and for athletic accomplishment. Gradually the students altered the jacket to make it look more stylish. 

Back then, the blazers were often embellished with very beautiful black patterns, which was the main inspiration behind this piece. with 2 sleeves .
.
.
